data.title: Hawks' Kyle Korver dunks for first time in three years
data.meta_description: Kyle Korver dunked on Wednesday. He hadn't done so since the 2012-2013 season.
data.text:
Kyle Korver is one of, if not the, best pure 3-point shooter in the NBA. That being said, the 11-year veteran has never been known as a dynamic player.

Heading into the Hawks' Wednesday night contest against the Pacers, Korver had not successfully dunked in a game in three years. That changed on a second-quarter two-on-one fast break.

MORE: 2015 Dunk Contest entrants | Will LeBron finally compete in Dunk Contest?

The one-handed slam was just the 16th of his career.

The Hawks entered Wednesday with the best record in the Eastern Conference at 34-8 and winners of 13 straight.
